{
  "text": "-If the resource vector \u2206 = b i satisfies the new feasibility condition then the optimal basis of the problem (P ) is still the same as in (P). Hence, there is a closed form outcome of the problem (P ) as v(S \u222a {i}) = f B B \u22121 (b + \u2206). -Otherwise, the optimal solution and the basis of (P) are used as the starting point for the dual simplex algorithm to solve (P ) (see [CITATION_1] , for details on the dual simplex method).",
